# Drizzle migrations

When generating a migration after changing `src/db/schema`, **always pass `--name`** with a short, descriptive kebab-case slug.

```bash
pnpm db:generate -- --name add-archetype-slug
pnpm db:generate -- --name drop-deck-visibility
```

Do **not** run bare `pnpm db:generate` — Drizzle will auto-name files (e.g. `0007_damp_reavers.sql`), which is hard to review in git.

**Naming:**
- Describe the change, not the ticket: `add-cards-synced-at`, not `fix-db`
- One logical change per migration when possible
- Use kebab-case, no spaces

After generating, apply with `pnpm db:migrate`.
